rComments: Great lecturer with a good sense of humour, who provides awesome handouts. He can be a little hard to get a hold of outside of office hours, though, so make appointments well in advance of deadlines.

Prof Dresher is one of the rarities in U of T. He's very knowledgeable and humorous. Listening to his lectures is almost as good as taking painkillers. So next time you've got a headache, go to his class.
He's actually seems nice! a rare quality in profs...

very funny nice guy who's always smiling and teaches well with interesting lectures, well organized course contents, easy midterms and assignments however, final exam was a nightmare. Be prepared or die trying!

He teaches English Words. And he seems to be quite a nice guy who knows a lot about english words and its history. He is able to filter his language to be purely grade 5 comprehensible in my class. Now that is a skill that not every prof can do.
Hilarious. And a good prof too.
The rating below states that Prof. Dresher is "unable to teach."  It seems to me, however, that this student was more likely "unable to learn."  Dresher is an excellent instructor.

Uses non-phonology courses as a venue for disseminating phonological theory.  Highly intelligent, but equally opaque - cannot teach the "plebeian" masses - those of us without doctorate degrees in linguistics....
Insightful scholar with an impressive intellect.  It is a privilege to be taught by someone like this.
